The CPP Investment Board is a professional investment management organization based in Toronto. CPP Investment Board, a Crown corporation, manages the assets of the Canada Pension Plan.
The CPP Investment Board is a professional investment management organization based in Toronto. CPP Investment Board manages the assets of the Canada Pension Plan.

The  Chief Technology Officer (CTO) leads the Information Technology department for the Canadian Pension Planning Investment Board (CPP) operates out of the… MoreThe CPP Investment Board is a professional investment management organization based in Toronto. CPP Investment Board manages the assets of the Canada Pension Plan.

The  Chief Technology Officer (CTO) leads the Information Technology department for the Canadian Pension Planning Investment Board (CPP) operates out of the organization’s Toronto, ON corporate headquarters. The company uses EasyDNS as its Nameserver Provider. The department works closely with the Human Resources department to ensure the alignment of all HR department activities with HR objectives and IT strategy.



The Corporate Systems division designs, develops, administers, manages, and documents the organization’s database system and performs technical and analytical services for various departments. The team is responsible for maintaining systems that enable efficient and effective business processes.

Technical Services staff is made up of a team of Systems Administrators, Systems Engineers, and Operations staff responsible for systems management, service desk, storage area networking, database administration, and telecommunications systems.





