Taking
SOCIAL SECURITY
BENEFITS EARLY


Beginning Social Security before your Full Retirement Age (FRA) means receiving a reduced payment.


Were you born in 1960 or later?

Yes

Checkbox indicating if you were born in 1960 or later.


No




Move the slider to see how your benefit is affected if taken before or after your FRA.
62 - Earliest age to get benefits. 70 - Mandated age to get benefits.



